commitResults.messageBody:
App lacks the ability to Store information from
previous usage.

Each use is isolated from each other and data
is not brought forward

Add a Storage class to handle storage of data
into plain text as well as loading of said data
on start up

New Exception StorageSyntaxException created
to handle potential exception arising from
new Class.

Command refactored to Task in all instance to
better fit description.

Deadline and Event class: add LocalDateTime

Both class have been dealing with time as plain string, usage of dateTime
allow for future expandability

Let's add DateTime funcationality to both Deadline and Event class

Adding this allows for much easier and accurate comparison of time
compare to using plain string

commitResults.messageTitle: Add more OOP to code base
commitResults.messageBody:
Add Ui class and Command package

Parser class was handling all the logic for parsing as
well as Ui. Tasklist was handling Command logic on top
of being a datastructure.

Tasklist and Parser handles too many task which cause
messy monolithic codebase.

Extracting a Ui class and a Command package will help
the codebase be easier to read and follow.

Let's pull up these extra features into its own
unique class.

Refactored main to also handle basic logic flow.

Ability to filter task by keyword was added

Task list would get hard for users to search through if
list gets too large

Create a feature for filtering task by keyword using
simple String matching. Tasklist has new method find()
that filters through the ArrayList and returns String
of task that matches keyword. FindCommand also implmented
and added to Enum and Parser logic.

Feature was add on the same way other command like add
was implemented.
Add Java Doc for clear documentation for future reference

Fix the coding style of the code base to comply with
coding standards
Merge branch level 9 with the feature to filter task list
